# Network Protocols

A **network protocol** is a set of rules that defines how devices communicate over a network.

Without protocols, devices would not know how to exchange or interpret information.

For example, imagine two people speaking completely different languages.

```text
Person A: Punjabi
Person B: Japanese
```

Communication would be difficult without a common language.

Network protocols act as a common communication language for devices.

Some common network protocols are:

| Protocol | Purpose                                     |
| -------- | ------------------------------------------- |
| HTTP     | Web communication                           |
| HTTPS    | Secure web communication                    |
| TCP      | Reliable data transmission                  |
| UDP      | Fast connectionless communication           |
| IP       | Logical addressing and packet delivery      |
| DNS      | Converts domain names to IP addresses       |
| DHCP     | Automatically assigns network configuration |
| FTP      | File transfer                               |
| SSH      | Secure remote access                        |
| SMTP     | Sending email                               |

Different protocols perform different tasks during network communication.

