# Network Segment

A **network segment** is a section of a network where devices communicate using a shared communication medium or logical network connection.

Consider the following network:

```text
PC1 ----\
         \
PC2 ----- Switch
         /
PC3 ----/
```

The devices connected to the switch are part of the same local network.

Network segmentation divides a large network into smaller sections.

For example:

```text
Company Network
      |
      +------ HR Network
      |
      +------ Finance Network
      |
      +------ IT Network
```

Network segmentation provides several advantages:

* Improved network performance
* Reduced broadcast traffic
* Better network management
* Improved security
* Isolation of sensitive systems

Technologies such as **VLANs** can be used to logically segment networks.

For example:

```text
VLAN 10 -> HR Department
VLAN 20 -> Finance Department
VLAN 30 -> IT Department
```

Even if devices are connected to the same physical switch, VLANs can logically separate them into different networks.

